games.comment: C.J. Spiller's numbers made him look like a ninth-round pick rather than a No. 9 overall selection. He rushed for just 6 yards on 7 attempts, and also chipped in with 4 receptions for 8 receiving yards. Spiller took numerous losses, as his offensive line couldn't open up any lanes for him. No surprise there.    I'll have time to bash the Bills even further for the next 16 weeks. As for the Dolphins, they were nearly as anemic on offense, especially in the second half, where they had only 37 yards on their first 4 possessions.

C.J. Spiller also caught a score. He was given 4 touches and turned them into 19 yards. He might be able to serve as a decent gimmick player for the Seahawks, but it's doubtful that he'll turn into a major contributor.    As for the Jets, there was some fear that
